    "transcription": "“A paper has just been established at Brooklyn, Windham Co. called “The Unionist,” by Charles C. Burleigh, Esq. It is a red hot Abolitionist, and its columns are filled with the martyrdom of Miss Prudence Crandall. It has much to say of Col. Judson’s negro oppression law, Watkins’ cell, &amp;c. &amp;c. Instead of Unionist, the paper should have been called Divisionist, Rebellionist, Pull off your Hat to the Blackist, and Knock your Teeth down your Throatist; and the editor, instead of announcing his name as Chas. Burleigh, should say, “published by Hurly Burly, near Canterbury.”",
