  {
    "pid": "unionist--text-0361",
    "title": "Dr. Johnson witticism",
    "creator": null,
    "description": "Anecdote about Dr. Johnson",
    "source": "<em>The Unionist</em> 1834-04-10",
    "subject": "Humor; Miscellaneous Filler",
    "transcription": "<p>\n  Dr. Johnson having formed one at a whist party at Mrs. Thrale’s house, was\n  asked by the lady at the close of the evening, whether he had lost any thing.\n  “Nothing but my time,” replied the moralist.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n",
